1) Bounded context:- Micro services are nothing but small unit of work which can run independently. 
While dividing services into multiple micro services we need to identify the boundaries of the each services.

2) Configuration management:- If we are running a microservices application in different environments, There is tons of tons of configuration need to maintain.
how to simplify these configuration sessions. 

3) Dynamic Scale down and scale up:- We need to dynamically scale up or down services based on usages. 